</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1904]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[325,556,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volcanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[325,556,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Recchia volcanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[566,659,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[566,659,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1998" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1998" box="[817,1230,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abauna">
<emphasis box="[817,935,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. abauna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[945,1230,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1998) Revisao da tribo Aerenicini Lacordaire, 1872 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Arquivos de Zoologia, 35 (1), 1 - 133. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 35 i 1 p 1 - 133" type="journal article" year="1998">Martins &amp; Galileo, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the upper eye lobes distinctly wider, with more than 10 rows of ommatidia (
<figureCitation box="[851,936,1412,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,390,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,373,1816]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29, Mecometopus martinsi sp. nov., holotype female: 26, dorsal habitus; 27, ventral habitus; 28, lateral habitus; 29, head, frontal view. 30, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female, upper eye lobes. 31, Recchia lanei, holotype female, upper eye lobes. 32 – 33, Recchia procera, paratype female: 32, upper eye lobes; 33, elytral apices." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167721/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), by the pubescence on basal third of elytral disc not forming band, by the distal sixth of the elytra not entirely with whitish pubescence. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1210,1324,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abauna">
<emphasis box="[1210,1324,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. abauna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the upper eye lobes are narrower, with 5-6 rows of ommatidia (
<figureCitation box="[766,852,1484,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,306,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,301,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female: 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus; 36, lateral habitus. 37, Recchia abauna, paratype female. 38, Recchia procera, paratype female. 39, Recchia lanei, holotype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
), the pubescence on basal discal third of the elytra forms band, the distal sixth of the elytra is entirely covered with whitish pubescence. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Lane, 1939" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis box="[1306,1436,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. distincta</emphasis>
(Lane, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the upper eye lobes wider and with finer ommatidia (narrower and with coarser ommatidia). It can be separated from 
